Chotaa Notion - Project Documentation

Overview:
Chotaa Notion is a collaborative document editing platform inspired by Notion. It allows users to create, edit, and share documents in real time, with a modern and user-friendly interface.

Tech Stack:
Frontend:
- React (JSX, hooks) (Bun runtime)
- Vite
- Tailwind CSS
- Lucide React (icons)
- Firebase (auth, Firestore, storage)
- Socket.IO (real-time)
- BlockNote (rich text editor) +  Y-Sweet/Yjs (real-time sync)

Backend:
- Node.js (Bun runtime)
- Express
- Socket.IO
- Firebase Admin SDK
- CORS, dotenv

Features:
- Email/password and Google login
- Create, edit, delete, organize documents and folders
- Real-time collaboration (multiple users editing)
- Comments and sharing with permissions (viewer, editor, admin)
- Rich text editor
- Dashboard with recent documents and search
- Responsive design, dark/light theme
- Notifications and user profile management

System Design:
- Frontend connects to backend via Socket.IO for real-time updates, manages authentication and file operations.
- Backend manages stable socket connections.
- Firebase stores users, documents, folders, and handles authentication.

UI/UX:
- Clean, modern design with Tailwind CSS and Rubik font
- Followed 60-30-10 color theory for color scheme
- Sidebar navigation, dashboard, modals for actions
- Shows active users and live cursors
- Works on desktop and mobile

Performance:
Client:
- Virtual scrolling for large docs
- Lazy loading for pages
Server:
- Connection pooling
- Caching
- Rate limiting

Suggestions:
- Offline editing
- Document version history
- Push/email notifications
- Export/import options
- Advanced permissions
- AI features
- Mobile app

Getting Started:
1. Install dependencies (
    frontend: bun install, 
    backend: bun install
   )
2. Set up .env files for Firebase and API URLs
3. Run frontend (bun run dev) and
       backend (bun run)
4. Open the app in your browser

Folder Structure:
